const SEARCH_INDEX = [{"title": "Beast Master Class Guide", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/beast-master/", "text": "Beast Master Class Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Beast Master Tier C ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Berserker Class Guide", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/berserker/", "text": "Berserker Class Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Berserker Tier C ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Cardinal Class Guide", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/cardinal/", "text": "Cardinal Class Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Cardinal Tier B ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Corruptor Class Guide", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/corruptor/", "text": "Corruptor Class Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Corruptor Tier D ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Deadeye Class Guide", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/deadeye/", "text": "Deadeye Class Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Deadeye Tier D ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Magus Class Guide", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/magus/", "text": "Magus Class Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Magus Tier B ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Marksman Class Guide", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/marksman/", "text": "Marksman Class Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Marksman Tier D ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Master Breeder Class Guide", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/master-breeder/", "text": "Master Breeder Class Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Master Breeder Tier A ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Mercenary Class Guide", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/mercenary/", "text": "Mercenary Class Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Mercenary Tier D ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Oracle Class Guide", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/oracle/", "text": "Oracle Class Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Oracle Tier D ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Overlord Class Guide", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/overlord/", "text": "Overlord Class Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Overlord Tier A ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Slayer Class Guide", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/slayer/", "text": "Slayer Class Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Slayer Tier D ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Templar Class Guide", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/templar/", "text": "Templar Class Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Templar Tier B ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Void Mage Class Guide", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/void-mage/", "text": "Void Mage Class Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Void Mage Tier S ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "War Kahuna Class Guide", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/war-kahuna/", "text": "War Kahuna Class Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home War Kahuna Tier C ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "175 and beyond", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/175-and-beyond/", "text": "175 and beyond - Rappelz Codex RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home 175 and Beyond Level 175 - 180: Devildom (DD) Devildom is the primary farming dungeon for this level range. Enter via the Kaia chain quest. Difficulty Experience Notes DD2 1 hour SS = 20% exp You should be able to solo this easily with previous setup. DD3 Much faster exp Possible for most classes - easier for some than others. Class-dependent difficulty. DD4 Highest difficulty Completely different scale. Don't get demotivated if you can't clear yet. Key Drops: Crystals for gear upgrades and DD accessories (8 types that you must collect same as you did for Circus Accessories: Spirit, Undead, Mecca, Beasts, Ains, Dragons, Devils, Antique) Priority: Daily DD runs | Rupee farming | Acquire PW gear for your main class | Upgrade skill cards to +6/+7 Gear Target: At this phase you should be focusing on your dailies DD1/2/3, farming Rupees, finding better PW gear with your main class skill, and getting your skill cards +6/+7. Once you do all of this, farm Rupees to buy Lava gear set (sometimes sold for 25B per piece - Head, Armor, Gloves, Boots) which is a universal upgrade usable for your future classes and can boost your damage by an insane amount. - Lava weapon can be sold for 35B to 50B. Buy buffs for 5B from Players => I can't stress enough how important this is. Once you test it you will be addicted to these buffs forever. Target Gear for Level 175-180 Equipment Specifications Belt Yushiva 8-slot (Antique stone) Weapon +20 (1/32), upgrade to +25 (32/32) over time Defense P.def not important past ~75k. Focus on Evasion: 8k+ (DE/Slayer), 4k+ (others) Helmet +22 minimum with +2 all skills Boss Cards Devil Skeleton (+30% damage type) | Reviac (+100 CP, -100% Crit) | P.Hector / M.Hector Level 180 - 190 If you're able to solo DD4/DD5 after following the previous steps and meeting the target gear requirements, then you can level yourself all the way to 195 in less than 2 weeks. Your goal would be the following: - Crafting Sand Cloak (equipable lvl 190) - Crafting Reviac Gear => crafting guide is in official Discord If you leveled yourself then you will already have 50% of the needed materials to craft the gear. Always upgrade armor first:. Upgrade Path Priority Notes Boots, Gloves, Helmet Keep Current Maintain Nusy gear for these slots Armor TOP PRIORITY Upgrade path: Nusy > Flumi > Inferno > Reviac Reviac Helmet 2nd Priority Provides +10% evasion bonus Remaining Gear 3rd Priority Complete Reviac set after armor and helmet Target Gear for Level 180-190 Equipment Specifications Cloak Sand Cloak +20 (upgrade with Dark Cubes) Armor Full Reviac Gear with main class skill +1 Belt Yushiva Antique 8-slot (+22 minimum) Weapon +24 or higher Helmet +24 minimum Decorative gear Full Lava Set ( without cloak & Mask since they are expensive and you can aim to craft them yourself once you hit 200+ by doing Vulcano dailies Rings +20 CP from Island of Gods, Awakened with CP Accessories Full DD Accessories (all 8 types), Awakened with CP Cards Devil Skeleton, Reviac Card, Hector/Lunacy Level 190 - 220 If you don't have the gear listed above, you won't be able to do much in SF. Farming all of this will allow you to solo DD6 and level yourself all the way to 200+. Target Gear for Level 190-210 Equipment Specifications Accessories Sky Set (accessories + Chaos Stone), enhanced with your main stat. Stop at +6 or +7. Helmet Luciad Iron Mask with +20 CP Craftables Cloak, Advanced Wings, Mask - all gained from Vulcanos 210 x10 daily runs Progression Note: veteran players choose to join a powerlevel from 190 to 220 because it is the fastest and most efficient way to gain a boost in stats, more access to TPs, and unlocking Maze/SF and TU dailies ASAP. The other alternative is to join a guild and do SF runs together until you hit 220. . RAPPELZ CODEX - Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Beyond Master Class", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/beyond-master-class/", "text": "Beyond Master Class RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Beyond Master Class Level progression from 153 to 175 with optimized gear and farming strategies. Level 153–160: Early Endgame Choose one of the following methods based on your class strength and gear: Method Location Difficulty Description Method 1 UG Quests Easy Take from village teleport NPCs. Pop Stamina Saver and Growth potions. Spam UG 2 Palmir until level 160. Method 2 Snow Basin Medium Kill dragons until level 160. Best for Void Mage or Berserker (AoE abilities make it easier to kite). Method 3 Labyrinth Dungeon Medium Do quests to final boss summoning Butkada and Akshas. Take quest → kill boss → abandon. +5% exp per run. Method 4 Island of Gods Hard & Fast Buy Boarding Pass from Black Marketer. 30-min solo to level 160. Not recommended for new players - alts only. Level 160–175: Gear Progression Checklist Step Item / Set Details 1 PW Gear Set From the farming above you are surely able to buy PW set from Auction House. The set is called: - Daman - For Hunters - Mach - For Warriors - Nemon - For Mages - Skadi - For Summoners. Buy Boots, Armor, Gloves - prefer 3-slot, cheapest possible. 2 Pets & Belt Death Tyrant 150 (+1 skill) | Bear Belt with passives + Gaia/Asura/Deva skills. Oracle: look for Passive + beneficial effects. 3 Helmet & Awakening Make Helmet R2+20 from Moonlight Dungeon. Awaken with Awakening Stones (Black Marketer Nostra Family). 4 Unity & Potion Wind Pixie / Ethereal Pixie / Bloodthirster (class-dependent). Spam use as level 1 potion every hour. Best Leveling Location: Remains of Ancients (RoA) To enter: Complete a quest at Circus 3 (starts at City of Ruins Hector NPC). If you followed the previous steps, RoA will be easy for you. Farm here for an hour or more - this step defines your future leveling speed for years to come. Circus Drops (Game Changers) Circus 3 drops Necklace + Earrings with bonus damage and damage reduction to mobs. Highest priority types: Undead, Beast, and Mecca. You'll need 2 earrings + 1 necklace of the same type to switch depending on the mobs you face in RoA. Pro tip: If your class can handle Circus 4, go for it - the drops are much better. Target Gear for RoA Farming Equipment Specifications Weapon +12 Circus with Accuracy stat (Mystic Jewel +500 ATK from Alvaria). Awakened with Weapon Stones. Accessories Earrings + Necklace (multiple types). Awakened with Accessory Stones. Rings Circus Rings with effects (+ATK or +stats) Belt Bear Belt +1 (4-slot). Easy to make with Belt Upgrader Kit drops. Armor PW gear +7 Pets 3 Pets + Boss Card setup. New pet level 150. Cards Lunacy or Mephisto Card Farming Island of Gods for weapons/accessories 170+, or buy from AH ✓ With this setup: Solo RoA even in Hector Room and level to 175. With a friend having the same gear, you can do HRoA First Room. What’s Next? Ready to continue your journey beyond level 175? Check out the 175 and beyond guide for the complete progression roadmap. RAPPELZ CODEX - Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Boss Card Collection", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/boss-card-collection/", "text": "Boss Card Collection RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Boss Card Collection This is something new players ignore while it has as high impact as a weapon +20 or even more. Easy to get boss cards from Flea. Boss Cards Overview Boss Card Qty Bonuses Obsidicar x7 +200 M.ATK MicroRaptor x5 +150 P.ATK , +150 M.ATK Mephisto x5 +10 Crit Power , +2% Crit Rate Lilith x5 +200 P.ATK , +200 M.ATK Ent x3 +150 P.ATK Yushiva x3 +5000 HP , +5000 MP Devil Slaughter x3 +200 P.ATK , +200 M.ATK Stone Gargoyle x3 +200 P.ATK , +200 M.ATK Devil Reviac x3 +30 Crit Power , +300 P.ATK , +300 M.ATK Dark Alchemist Saragon x3 +10% Crit Rate , +450 P.ATK , +450 M.ATK Bloodthirsty Beast Karmos x3 +50 VIT , +2000 Max HP Shadow of Reaper Necro x3 +50 STR , +50 INT Final Combined Stats Stat Value Physical Attack +1650 P.ATK Magic Attack +1700 M.ATK Critical Rate +12% Critical Power +40 Max HP +7000 Max MP +5000 Vitality +50 VIT Strength +50 STR Intelligence +50 INT 💰 Cost Estimate: 5-7 billion rupees A huge free boost compared to other upgrades. Feel free to check the Boss card discord channel for more bonuses that are not mentioned here. Complete Boss Card Collection Below is the full list of all 61 boss cards organized by rarity. Collecting all cards requires 358 cards total . Normal (x10 Cards — 14 Boss Cards = 140 Cards) Boss Card Bonuses Baron Madius P Atk +30 Emmanuel Raymond Cast Spd +2 Ultimate Witch M Def +30 Bear Mother Critical Rate +2 Oforia P Def +30 Abhuva Evasion +5 Primal Scream M Atk +50 Taranida P Atk +50 Crustalino Atk Spd +3 Likirus M Atk +80 Soulseeker P Acc +5 Takin Max Weight +100 Lucius M Acc +5 Silex the Giant Max HP +150 Rare (x7 Cards — 13 Boss Cards = 91 Cards) Boss Card Bonuses Kiscia the Beautiful P Atk +80 , P Acc +5 Lady Ruina P Acc +10 Aurumis P Atk +100 Dominatus the Mad M Atk +80 , M Acc +5 Queen Eratia M Def +100 Ilrios Max HP +200 , Max Weight +200 Betrayal Max HP +200 , Max MP +100 Ashmaw the Devourer M Atk +100 , Cast Spd +3 Sand Lord Kynish P Def +100 Draka Atk Spd +3 , Max HP +100 Queen Eva Evasion +10 , P Acc +5 Obsidicar M Atk +200 Vulcanus Creature Taming +1 Lvl Special (x5 Cards — 15 Boss Cards = 75 Cards) Boss Card Bonuses Butkadah M Def +150 , M Acc +5 Medusa Block Def +200 , P Def +150 Black Widow P Def +150 , M Def +150 Microraptor P Atk +150 , M Atk +150 Bone Dragon M Def +150 , Max MP +300 Mephisto Critical Rate +2 , Critical Power +10 Lilith P Atk +200 , M Atk +200 Soul of Lunacy P Def +150 , Max HP +500 Ent P Atk +150 , Atk Spd +2 Cruel Tula HP Recovery +200 , MP Recovery +200 Lion Max HP +100 , Max MP +100 Barga Evasion +15 , M Res +15 Kraken P Def +150 , Max HP +50 Red Eye Troll Hunter Max HP +2,500 , P Def +1,000 Cruel Troll Hunter Critical Power +10 , P Atk +250 , M Atk +250 Unique (x3 Cards — 14 Boss Cards = 42 Cards) Boss Card Bonuses Courage of Grand Master Hector P Atk +500 , Max HP +500 , P Acc +15 Knowledge of Grand Master Hector M Atk +500 , Max MP +300 , M Acc +15 Crystal Golem P Def +500 , M Def +200 , Max HP +1,500 Bloodthirsty Slaughterer M Def +500 , P Def +200 , Max MP +1,000 Yushiva Max HP +5,000 , Max MP +3,000 , Max Weight +500 Wooden Devil P Pierce +150 , M Pierce +150 Devil Slaughterer P Atk +200 , M Atk +200 Stone Gargoyle P Atk +200 , M Atk +200 Magma Golem Max HP +300 , Max MP +300 Crazy Hagen Block Def +300 , P Def +100 , M Def +100 Devil Reviac Critical Power +30 , P Atk +300 , M Atk +300 Devil Skeleton Crit Pow +20 , P Atk +350 , M Atk +350 , Crit Rate +5 Dark Alchemist Saragon Crit Rate +10 , P Atk +450 , M Atk +450 Bloodthirsty Beast Karmos VIT +50 , P Def +2,000 Epic (x2 Cards — 5 Boss Cards = 10 Cards) Boss Card Bonuses Chaotic Phoenix: Warrior P Atk +5% Chaotic Phoenix: Magician M Atk +5% Chaotic Phoenix: Summoner STR +30 , VIT +30 , INT +30 , Crit Pow +20 Shadow of Reaper, Necron STR +50 , INT +50 Butcher Vulcan Critical Power +30 , P Pierce +500 , M Pierce +500 Max Achievable Stats (All 61 Cards Collected) Stat Value STR 80 INT 80 VIT 80 Physical Attack 3,010 + 5% Magical Attack 3,220 + 5% Physical Defense 4,530 Magical Defense 1,380 Physical Accuracy 40 Magical Accuracy 30 Attack Speed 8 Cast Speed 5 Max HP 11,100 Max MP 5,100 HP Recovery 200 MP Recovery 200 Critical Rate 19 Critical Power 90 Evasion 30 M Res 15 P Pierce 650 M Pierce 650 Block Defense 500 Max Weight 800 Creature Taming +1 Lvl Total Cards Needed: Normal = 14 Boss Cards (140 cards) | Rare = 13 Boss Cards (91 cards) | Special = 15 Boss Cards (75 cards) Unique = 14 Boss Cards (42 cards) | Epic = 5 Boss Cards (10 cards) Grand Total = 61 Boss Cards — 358 Cards for Collection RAPPELZ CODEX - Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "General Tips and Tricks", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/general-tips/", "text": "General Tips and Tricks RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home General Tips & Tricks Essential advice for efficient leveling, gear progression, and gameplay optimization. Strategic Leveling Tips Tip Key Point Survivability over Damage Most players rush for damage but then complain about dying. Prioritize survivability while gearing up at low levels. A Soul of Lunacy card is one of the cheapest and best choices for most classes without healing skills. Vulc Questline Timing Start the daily Vulc questline early. Koala spawns can be unpredictable, and you need the Koala quest to unlock 190+ Vulc content and get free +1 upgrade cubes. Keep R2+20 Helmet Hold onto your R2+20 helmet and keep gear in Distorted (160) until you can afford a +20 Medusa/Nusy helmet. The +1 all skills bonus is worth more than the set bonus. Farm at RoA Until 180 Stay at Remains of Ancients until level 180. Well-geared players can kill in Hard Mode RoA by level 175. Killing snowmen or in Hector room drops 1-3 cubes for passive income, which also covers crafting materials later. Free vs Paid Powerlevels Avoid spending Rupees on powerlevels, but always take free ones. They're most impactful in the Smart Vendor Choices Sell ND (non-disassembleable) weapons and armor to vendors, but disassemble or altar dura gear. Crit power deco pieces from the altar are far more valuable than vendor rupees, especially before getting Lava gear. Gameplay Optimization Mechanic How It Works Gnoll Buff 30%/40%/50% damage reflection reduces damage taken by 3%/4%/5%. Very helpful buff for survivability in harder dungeons. Camper Title Reduces damage taken. Buy a tent from the merchant to earn this title. Weapon Awakening Always awaken weapons and accessories with Awakening Stones. Keep weapons with the best bonus for future use. Universal Upgrades Priority Prioritize universal upgrades over class-specific gear (Lava Set, Helmet +24, Emblem, Yushiva Belt). You never know when you'll want to change classes. Purse Purchases Buy Purse of Bright Powers (non-pet classes) or Purse of Invocations (pet classes) for 500 Cash Shop coins - the bonus is worth the investment. Enhanced Crystal Glasses Cheap item equippable from level 1: +10 all stats, +40 luck. Get from AH for ~25M (drops from HRoA snowman Hector room). Get it ASAP. Arena Currency Once committed to a main, do daily Arena quests. 20k Arena points = Traveling Gear (4% all stats) from Arena Merchant Jana at Rondo. Worth the grind. RAPPELZ CODEX - Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Getting Started in Rappelz", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/getting-started/", "text": "Getting Started in Rappelz RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Getting Started in Rappelz Everything a new player needs: early leveling zones, buffs, quests and more. Starting Your Character If you have 0 Rupies on your account, follow these steps first. Note: It's recommended that you walk through the quests of Trainee Island to get a feel of the game the first time if you don't want to skip the initial steps outlined below. Initial Setup Teleport to Hidden Village and go to the merchant then sell everything in your bag. This will get you more than 7,000 Rupees needed for buffs and traveling to Moonlight Dungeon. Put Rupies in Warehouse and delete your character, then create a new one. Go to the Buffer NPC and take the free buff and the 7,000 Rupee Buff. Leveling Phases Level Range Location / Method Notes 1–10 Moonlight Dungeon Exterior Kill 3 mobs outside while using Stamina Saver and a growth potion. 10–50 Moonlight Dungeon Interior Continue leveling inside Moonlight Dungeon. 50 Class Change Teleport to Hidden Village and talk to the Class Master. If broke, sell Extreme Essence at the Flea Market. 50–105 Crystal Valley (Hard Mode) Find the Koala and enter Hard mode. Stay until level 105. Do your 2nd class change at the Class Master. 105–120 Red Farm or Witch Quest 1 RedFarm: Rondo Guild NPC | Witch Quest 1: Katan Guild NPC. Complete second class change first. 120–138 Sanctuary Questline Complete the Sanctuary questline. Quest starts at Rondo Merchant NPC. 138–150 Witch Quest 2 Quest starts at Horizon Hector NPC. 150–153 Master Class Trials Complete Master Class Trials. Quest starts at Hector. Self-Sufficient Progression If you don't want to rely on other players to progress: Go to Sanctuary Hidden and farm items with the [Witch] type because they have better stats. Take 120 items and make them +12 without breaking them, then attempt an Ancient Cube for a chance at getting +17. If you have full [Witch] equipment at level 120, all +12 or more, you will be stronger than anyone using level 150 gear at +7. This means your future characters will be able to skip Sanctuary quests entirely because you'll one-shot mobs in Sanctuary Hidden from level 105 to 133. What's Next? Once you reach level 153 and complete the Master Class Trials, you're ready for endgame progression. Head over to our Beyond Master Class guide to learn about gear requirements and strategies to push further. RAPPELZ CODEX - Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Pet Taming", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/pet-taming/", "text": "Pet Taming RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Pet Taming In order to increase your pet taming chance, there are multiple items you need to acquire. Each one increases your taming chance by +1% . Taming Chance Items Item Bonus Image Enhanced Glasses +1% Taming Crystal Sword +1% Taming Emblem +1% Taming Luciad's Iron Mask +1% Taming Taming Rings from Circus (x2) +2% Taming Bear Belt +1% Taming DT Buff +1% Taming — Helmet +24 +1% Taming — Vulcano Boss Card Collection +1% Taming RAPPELZ CODEX - Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Rupee Farming", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/rupee-farming/", "text": "Rupee Farming RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Rupee Farming There are different ways to farm rupees in the game. Snow Basin — Kill dragons and sell Lucky Cubes at the Flea Market. Farming at Lake Kaia or Pig's Spot . The Farming Principle The principle of farming is very simple: the more Luck stat you have, the more drops you get. This is why Beast Master is the best class to farm rupees — its skill Harmony of Life allows you to transform into your summoned pet and gain bonus stats, including Luck . Try taming Unique Humans in the Parallel World dungeon and stage the one you get as a tank pet (it has the highest stats). Then you can summon 2 Wind Pixies S0 Lv160, equipped with 2H Maces + Shield. Target Setup for Farming Slot Item / Pet Main Pet Human Tank S5 (you can start with an S0 or any pet just to get going) Summons 2 Wind Pixies Lv160 — for better gear equipment options Helmet Enhanced Glasses Rings +40 Luck Rings x2 (droppable at Lake Kaia) Armor Set Ergon Set — droppable in Ancient Magic Lab (Fanatics), gives 10% Luck Accessory Luminous Feather (+50 Luck) Belt Pets 2x Snowman S0 Lv90 + 2x Kenta S0 Lv90 Weapons 2x Royal Axe Buff 5B Buff from other players — provides more stats to you and your pets, including more Luck. You'll earn back the 5B in 2 to 3 hours, then use Refresh Scrolls on yourself and your pets. This step is not mandatory, but I highly recommend it! Playstyle Your Beast Master will be running through mobs — they will keep dying before you even reach them, because the 2 Wind Pixies auto-attack from range. Perma running, no stopping, easier looting. RAPPELZ CODEX - Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Lake Kaia Zone Guide", "cat": "Map", "url": "map/lake-kaia/", "text": "Lake Kaia Zone Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Lake Kaia ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Pig's Spot Zone Guide", "cat": "Map", "url": "map/pigs-spot/", "text": "Pig's Spot Zone Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Pig's Spot ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Remains of the Ancients", "cat": "Map", "url": "map/remains-of-the-ancients/", "text": "Remains of the Ancients RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Remains of the Ancients With the release of Epic 9.3 a new dungeon was added: “Remains of the Ancients”. Along with two new TP Quests, both of which can be started at 160. However, one can only be completed once the player has reached level 170. After reaching level 160, players can accept a quest from Warrior Hector in City of Ruins which begins a series of quests allowing them to enter the Remains of the Ancients. However, the final quest can only be completed once the player reaches 170 and returns to Warrior Hector. After completing this quest, players will receive an additional TP point. Quest Walkthrough Head to Rondo to find Armor Trader Bella. Kill Lilith in stage 3 or 4 of the Red Spider Circus to acquire a Bright Piece of Fabric (this may take a few attempts) and give it to Armor Trader Bella. Once you hand in the Fabric you will be given a Cute Doll. Head back to City of Ruins (you won’t be given a quest) and talk to Witch’s Child Xabi who is located right next to Warrior Hector. Accept that quest then talk to her again to turn it in (she takes the Cute Doll from you). Talk to Warrior Hector again before heading to Mare Village to talk with Charmer Kisha. Accept the quest from her and kill a Starving Slaughter, which can be found wandering around outside Mare Village. Return to Charmer Kisha and turn the quest in, accept her new quest and head back to Warrior Hector in City of Ruins. Accept his quest and head to the Red Spider Circus again. Kill Soul of Lunacy in either stages 3 or 4 and acquire the Remaining Trace (this could take a few attempts like Lilith). After acquiring the Remaining Trace, return to Warrior Hector. Talk to Witch’s Child Xabi, accept her quest and she will give you a Defense Force Token — this item will allow you to enter the Remains of the Ancients. Finally talk to Hector again to accept the last part of the quest; you will be tasked with acquiring a Bloody Report from Grandmaster Hector in the Remains of the Ancients. Once this part has been completed, if you have not yet reached level 170 Hector will no longer have anything to say to you. After reaching 170 and returning to Hector you will be able to finish this quest line and receive an additional TP. Dungeon Map RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "SnowBasin Zone Guide", "cat": "Map", "url": "map/snowbasin/", "text": "SnowBasin Zone Guide RAPPELZ CODEX ← Back to Home ← Back to Home SnowBasin ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ CODEX — Fan-made community guide"}];
